{"questionId":"28483","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Resistor R is connected in a circuit with a cell that has internal resistance.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/84afac67fd13bd630c3b60e279694bf792ddcffb.png\"></p>\n<p>The ammeter and the voltmeter are ideal.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The cell has an emf of 1.49 V. The resistance of R is 50.0 Ω. The voltmeter reads 1.47 V.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the total power dissipated in the circuit.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>49</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0438</mn></math> «W»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept use of 0.7 Ω in <strong>MP1</strong>.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28483","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.5b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the total power dissipated in the circuit.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Top